1
00:00:04,583 --> 00:00:05,540
♪ Men. ♪

2
00:00:05,627 --> 00:00:07,586
Hey, Louis, check it out.

3
00:00:07,673 --> 00:00:10,371
This app will help you learn
how to speak Mandarin Chinese.

4
00:00:10,458 --> 00:00:12,373
Are you sending me to China?

5
00:00:12,460 --> 00:00:14,593
No, I'd never do that.

6
00:00:14,680 --> 00:00:16,725
He sent his kid to Japan.

7
00:00:16,812 --> 00:00:17,770
Oh, no, no.

8
00:00:17,857 --> 00:00:19,598
The-the Army sent him to Japan.

9
00:00:19,685 --> 00:00:21,643
You're sending me to the Army?

10
00:00:21,730 --> 00:00:23,036
No, no, n-no.

11
00:00:23,123 --> 00:00:24,342
We're not sending you anywhere.

12
00:00:24,429 --> 00:00:25,821
We-we just want
to help you learn.

13
00:00:25,908 --> 00:00:27,084
So, check it out.

14
00:00:27,171 --> 00:00:29,260
You can type in any phrase,

15
00:00:29,347 --> 00:00:32,219
and the app will say it for you.

16
00:00:32,306 --> 00:00:35,614
[woman speaking
Mandarin Chinese]

17
00:00:35,701 --> 00:00:36,745
Ooh, what'd she say?

18
00:00:36,832 --> 00:00:38,225
She sounds pretty.

19
00:00:38,312 --> 00:00:39,487
She said,
"Alan, your fly is open."

20
00:00:39,574 --> 00:00:41,359
Oh. Oh!

21
00:00:41,446 --> 00:00:43,230
[chuckles] Uh, well, how do you
tell her, "Thank you"?

22
00:00:43,317 --> 00:00:45,189
Uh, let's find out.

23
00:00:46,320 --> 00:00:48,235
Xiexie.

24
00:00:48,322 --> 00:00:51,717
That's gonna blow their minds
down at the Panda Express.

25
00:00:51,804 --> 00:00:54,459
Extra orange chicken, xiexie.

26
00:00:54,546 --> 00:00:57,288
Walden, I-I'm Chinese Elvis.

27
00:00:57,375 --> 00:00:58,767
Xiexie.Xiexie, very much.

28
00:00:58,854 --> 00:00:59,768
[chuckles]

29
00:00:59,855 --> 00:01:00,987
All right.

30
00:01:01,074 --> 00:01:02,989
Let's put on these headphones,

31
00:01:03,076 --> 00:01:06,297
and we'll learn
a little Chinese, huh?

32
00:01:06,384 --> 00:01:08,647
So, um, listen,
g-going forward,

33
00:01:08,734 --> 00:01:11,215
um, how are we gonna do
this whole co-parenting thing?

34
00:01:11,302 --> 00:01:12,825
What do you mean?

35
00:01:12,912 --> 00:01:14,609
Well, when you were gonna
adopt a baby,

36
00:01:14,696 --> 00:01:16,481
we were gonna get
a divorce right after.

37
00:01:16,568 --> 00:01:19,353
But now, if we become
Louis's foster parents,

38
00:01:19,440 --> 00:01:21,399
we're gonna have to be together
for a minimum of six months.

39
00:01:21,486 --> 00:01:23,052
Uh, not that I'm complaining.

40
00:01:23,140 --> 00:01:24,663
This is the happiest
and most loving of any

41
00:01:24,750 --> 00:01:26,621
of my three marriages.

42
00:01:26,708 --> 00:01:27,970
I'm thinking it would
just be the opposite

43
00:01:28,057 --> 00:01:29,668
of when Jake was here.

44
00:01:29,755 --> 00:01:31,235
You were the dad, and
I occasionally imparted wisdom,

45
00:01:31,322 --> 00:01:33,846
like... the skull
and crossbones on a bottle

46
00:01:33,933 --> 00:01:36,414
underneath the sink doesn't mean
that it's pirate juice.

47
00:01:36,501 --> 00:01:39,112
Okay, well, uh, uh,

48
00:01:39,199 --> 00:01:41,114
then I will follow
your lead with Louis.

49
00:01:41,201 --> 00:01:43,769
I will be the second
in command, the-the copilot,

50
00:01:43,856 --> 00:01:46,989
the, uh, the, uh,
the lieutenant, if you will.

51
00:01:47,076 --> 00:01:48,426
I won't.

52
00:01:49,731 --> 00:01:51,603
This is hard.

53
00:01:51,690 --> 00:01:53,170
Oh, all right,
let me help you out here.

54
00:01:53,257 --> 00:01:54,693
Type in a phrase.

55
00:01:54,780 --> 00:01:56,129
Anything you want to say.

56
00:01:58,218 --> 00:01:59,132
Okay.

57
00:01:59,219 --> 00:02:01,961
"I... want to quit."

58
00:02:04,181 --> 00:02:05,791
Okay, uh...

59
00:02:07,096 --> 00:02:08,968
[speaks Mandarin Chinese]

60
00:02:10,665 --> 00:02:12,145
Uh, excuse me.

61
00:02:12,232 --> 00:02:13,799
If you're trying to say,
"I want to quit,"

62
00:02:13,886 --> 00:02:16,367
it's pronounced...
[speaks Mandarin Chinese]

63
00:02:16,454 --> 00:02:19,370
What you asked for is
a lap dance.

64
00:02:19,457 --> 00:02:21,546
Oh, my God, I'm sorry.

65
00:02:21,633 --> 00:02:23,156
It's okay, I wasn't offended.

66
00:02:23,243 --> 00:02:25,506
Oh, well, in that case...

67
00:02:25,593 --> 00:02:27,160
[repeats mispronunciation]

68
00:02:27,247 --> 00:02:28,814
[laughs]

69
00:02:28,901 --> 00:02:29,815
I'm Jean.

70
00:02:29,902 --> 00:02:30,903
I'm Walden.

71
00:02:32,296 --> 00:02:34,167
Oh, and, uh, this is
Louis and Alan.

72
00:02:34,254 --> 00:02:36,082
Hi. Nice to meet you.

73
00:02:36,169 --> 00:02:38,389
So, you're teaching Louis
Mandarin?

74
00:02:38,476 --> 00:02:41,261
Well, I bought him, uh,
an app for 99 cents,

75
00:02:41,348 --> 00:02:43,698
so, yeah, I'm teaching him.

76
00:02:43,785 --> 00:02:46,005
[laughs]

77
00:02:46,092 --> 00:02:49,487
Well, I speak fluent Mandarin,
so if you need any help

78
00:02:49,574 --> 00:02:52,533
with anything...

79
00:02:52,620 --> 00:02:54,187
give me a call.

80
00:02:54,274 --> 00:02:57,103
Ah, well, I could always use
a helping hand.

81
00:02:57,190 --> 00:02:58,104
[chuckles]

82
00:03:00,193 --> 00:03:02,891
[speaking Mandarin Chinese]

83
00:03:02,978 --> 00:03:05,503
Oh. Oh!

84
00:03:07,940 --> 00:03:10,029
Nice meeting you.

85
00:03:11,900 --> 00:03:13,685
What happened?

86
00:03:13,772 --> 00:03:15,513
What did you say?

87
00:03:15,600 --> 00:03:17,732
He said,
"They're married."

88
00:03:17,819 --> 00:03:21,083
And if he hadn't,
I was about to.

89
00:03:21,170 --> 00:03:24,130
♪ Men, men, men, men, manly men,
men, men ♪

90
00:03:24,217 --> 00:03:26,654
♪ Ah.
♪ Men.
♪ Men.

91
00:03:29,570 --> 00:03:30,789
♪ Men. ♪

92
00:03:30,876 --> 00:03:32,530
How's it going
out there?

93
00:03:32,617 --> 00:03:34,183
I don't know. I'm trying
to read their lips.

94
00:03:34,271 --> 00:03:35,924
He either said, "I
really like it here,"

95
00:03:36,011 --> 00:03:37,796
or "I'd really
like a beer."

96
00:03:39,363 --> 00:03:40,886
I-I'm sure
he's saying good things.

97
00:03:40,973 --> 00:03:42,540
You know, how-how you're
teaching him Chinese,

98
00:03:42,627 --> 00:03:45,325
how I'm teaching him
environmental awareness.

99
00:03:45,412 --> 00:03:47,719
You taught him to pee in
the shower to save water.

100
00:03:47,806 --> 00:03:50,678
And you know what
our Mother Earth says to that?

101
00:03:50,765 --> 00:03:52,245
Xiexie.

102
00:03:54,334 --> 00:03:57,555
I got to tell you, I've already
grown attached to this kid.

103
00:03:57,642 --> 00:03:59,470
And if she does try
to take him away,

104
00:03:59,557 --> 00:04:01,689
I know a guy
who can get him back.

105
00:04:01,776 --> 00:04:03,343
You're kidding, right?

106
00:04:03,430 --> 00:04:05,737
Right, kidding.

107
00:04:05,824 --> 00:04:09,697
But if I find an envelope in my
car with, say, two grand in it,

108
00:04:09,784 --> 00:04:12,004
I have no way of knowing
where it came from.

109
00:04:13,527 --> 00:04:14,659
Can I talk to you guys
for a second?

110
00:04:14,746 --> 00:04:16,400
Uh, yeah, sure.

111
00:04:16,487 --> 00:04:17,836
Uh, Berta, could
you watch Louis?

112
00:04:17,923 --> 00:04:19,533
Absolutely.

113
00:04:19,620 --> 00:04:21,361
We'll be in the car
with the engine running.

114
00:04:21,448 --> 00:04:22,493
No reason.

115
00:04:24,495 --> 00:04:27,236
So, I talked to Louis
about his weekend here.

116
00:04:27,324 --> 00:04:29,804
Uh, did he answer you
in English or Mandarin?

117
00:04:29,891 --> 00:04:31,937
English.

118
00:04:32,024 --> 00:04:33,721
Though I'm very impressed
you're teaching him Chinese.

119
00:04:33,808 --> 00:04:35,375
And to pee in the shower.

120
00:04:35,462 --> 00:04:37,595
That's mine.

121
00:04:37,682 --> 00:04:41,207
I'm also teaching him to dance
like no one is watching.

122
00:04:42,904 --> 00:04:45,951
Well, he seems to have
settled in nicely.

123
00:04:46,038 --> 00:04:48,214
He feels very happy
and safe with you guys,

124
00:04:48,301 --> 00:04:50,608
so I see no reason
why I shouldn't approve you

125
00:04:50,695 --> 00:04:51,957
to be Louis's foster parents.

126
00:04:52,044 --> 00:04:53,219
Really?
Are you serious?

127
00:04:53,306 --> 00:04:54,873
I rarely lie about these things.

128
00:04:54,960 --> 00:04:57,179
I did it once,
and it did not go well.

129
00:04:57,266 --> 00:04:59,138
This-this is great!

130
00:04:59,225 --> 00:05:02,359
I-I know. I-I've never been
approved for anything, ever.

131
00:05:02,446 --> 00:05:04,361
Bite me, Discover Card.

132
00:05:04,448 --> 00:05:06,319
Congratulations!
Thank you!

133
00:05:06,406 --> 00:05:08,277
This is my favorite part
of the job.

134
00:05:08,365 --> 00:05:10,192
Well, that and doughnut Friday.

135
00:05:10,279 --> 00:05:12,325
Oh, God, my life is empty.

136
00:05:12,412 --> 00:05:14,109
Oh, wait, d-does
Louis know?

137
00:05:14,196 --> 00:05:15,981
No, he thinks I'm happy.

138
00:05:17,548 --> 00:05:20,638
Oh, you mean about him here.

139
00:05:20,725 --> 00:05:22,161
Uh, no, you should tell him.

140
00:05:22,248 --> 00:05:24,511
But before you do,
just remember,

141
00:05:24,598 --> 00:05:27,471
kids who've been in the foster
system as long as he has can be

142
00:05:27,558 --> 00:05:29,211
a little withdrawn
or manipulative,

143
00:05:29,298 --> 00:05:31,126
so don't be surprised
if he acts out.

144
00:05:31,213 --> 00:05:33,302
It's okay. I was a
rebel when I was a kid.

145
00:05:33,390 --> 00:05:35,304
One night, I took my
mom's car for a joyride.

146
00:05:35,392 --> 00:05:37,481
[chuckles] The cops would
have never caught me

147
00:05:37,568 --> 00:05:40,353
if the library
hadn't been closed.

148
00:05:40,440 --> 00:05:41,789
Well, call me if
you need anything.

149
00:05:41,876 --> 00:05:43,965
I got to run. I got to
hit the craft store.

150
00:05:44,052 --> 00:05:47,926
I am making each one of my cats
a Christmas stocking.

151
00:05:48,013 --> 00:05:50,450
I should have stopped at
"I got to run."

152
00:05:50,537 --> 00:05:52,278
Anyway, congratulations.

153
00:05:54,193 --> 00:05:56,804
Oh, hey, uh, Louis,
could you come in here?

154
00:05:56,891 --> 00:05:59,285
Oh, my God, we should
tell him he can't stay.

155
00:05:59,372 --> 00:06:00,765
How funny would that be?

156
00:06:02,506 --> 00:06:04,595
I'll follow your lead.

157
00:06:06,379 --> 00:06:09,643
Hey, Louis, um,

158
00:06:09,730 --> 00:06:11,297
so Ms. McMartin said

159
00:06:11,384 --> 00:06:13,821
that you like it here
and you want to stay.

160
00:06:13,908 --> 00:06:14,822
I do.

161
00:06:14,909 --> 00:06:16,041
Well, we told her

162
00:06:16,128 --> 00:06:17,782
that we want you to stay,

163
00:06:17,869 --> 00:06:21,133
and she said... okay!

164
00:06:21,220 --> 00:06:22,656
Really? Cool!

165
00:06:22,743 --> 00:06:24,049
Yeah. We should celebrate.

166
00:06:24,136 --> 00:06:26,486
Can we get pizza, Zippy?

167
00:06:26,573 --> 00:06:28,314
[Berta laughs]

168
00:06:28,401 --> 00:06:30,272
That turned out funnier
than I thought it would.

169
00:06:32,536 --> 00:06:34,494
♪ Men.

170
00:06:34,581 --> 00:06:36,496
You know, when my
son was your age,

171
00:06:36,583 --> 00:06:38,672
we used to play video
games just like this.

172
00:06:38,759 --> 00:06:40,892
Really?
Yes, and I used
to let him win,

173
00:06:40,979 --> 00:06:42,328
just like I'm
letting you win...

174
00:06:42,415 --> 00:06:43,590
[cars crashing over TV]Hey!

175
00:06:43,677 --> 00:06:45,374
How'd you blow
up my car?

176
00:06:45,462 --> 00:06:48,377
All right, Louis,
time to get ready for bed.

177
00:06:48,465 --> 00:06:49,944
Five more minutes?

178
00:06:50,031 --> 00:06:51,772
No. You know the deal.

179
00:06:51,859 --> 00:06:53,992
One hour of video games a
night. Now it's bedtime.

180
00:06:54,079 --> 00:06:55,689
Aw, no fair.

181
00:06:55,776 --> 00:06:56,864
Well, life isn't fair.

182
00:06:56,951 --> 00:06:58,562
Look at my face, look at his.

183
00:06:58,649 --> 00:07:01,347
All right, I'm gonna go
run you a bath.

184
00:07:01,434 --> 00:07:04,045
Put your dishes in the sink
and put away the controllers.

185
00:07:04,132 --> 00:07:06,004
And, Louis, you help him.

186
00:07:09,834 --> 00:07:13,272
Oh, I know you're upset,
but rules are important.

187
00:07:13,359 --> 00:07:17,319
It's just, we never got to play
video games in the group home.

188
00:07:17,406 --> 00:07:20,322
Oh, of course.

189
00:07:20,409 --> 00:07:22,324
The group home.

190
00:07:24,457 --> 00:07:27,242
Okay, what if we just
snuck in a few more minutes?

191
00:07:27,329 --> 00:07:29,418
Really?
Yeah, yeah,
yeah, but, uh...

192
00:07:29,506 --> 00:07:30,898
but you can't
tell Walden,

193
00:07:30,985 --> 00:07:32,987
and we have to play
it really quietly.

194
00:07:33,074 --> 00:07:34,336
[quietly]:
You're the coolest.

195
00:07:34,423 --> 00:07:36,034
[gasps]
I'm the cool dad.

196
00:07:37,601 --> 00:07:39,428
[whispers]:
I'm the cool dad.

197
00:07:41,996 --> 00:07:44,433
♪ Men.

198
00:07:44,521 --> 00:07:45,739
Oh, hey
there, kiddo.

199
00:07:45,826 --> 00:07:46,610
How'd you sleep?

200
00:07:46,697 --> 00:07:48,568
With my eyes closed.

201
00:07:48,655 --> 00:07:50,396
Ah, kicking it old school.

202
00:07:50,483 --> 00:07:51,963
I respect that.

203
00:07:52,050 --> 00:07:53,312
Can I have breakfast?

204
00:07:53,399 --> 00:07:56,010
Sure. How about some oatmeal?

205
00:07:56,097 --> 00:07:57,577
Cookies!

206
00:07:57,664 --> 00:08:00,624
Well, do you like
oatmeal cookies?
Yes.

207
00:08:00,711 --> 00:08:02,408
Well, this is a sugarless
oatmeal cookie

208
00:08:02,495 --> 00:08:04,105
in wet, pasty form.

209
00:08:04,192 --> 00:08:05,933
Why can't I have cookies?

210
00:08:06,020 --> 00:08:07,761
Well, because
cookies aren't breakfast food.

211
00:08:07,848 --> 00:08:09,633
And remember what Walden said
about eating healthy.

212
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:11,548
Yeah, I know.

213
00:08:11,635 --> 00:08:15,073
My last foster family
wouldn't give me cookies either.

214
00:08:15,160 --> 00:08:16,683
Oh.

215
00:08:18,685 --> 00:08:21,079
I suppose one wouldn't hurt.

216
00:08:24,865 --> 00:08:26,475
Thanks.
[chuckles]

217
00:08:26,563 --> 00:08:28,086
WALDEN:
Hey, Louis, are you up yet?

218
00:08:28,173 --> 00:08:30,131
Oh. Uh, in here!

219
00:08:30,218 --> 00:08:31,916
