Eat it. Wipe your mouth.

220
00:08:33,047 --> 00:08:34,962
Chocolate lips sink ships.

221
00:08:35,049 --> 00:08:36,573
[singsongy]:
Morning.

222
00:08:36,660 --> 00:08:38,444
Morning. Just making Louis
some oatmeal.

223
00:08:38,531 --> 00:08:40,968
That's good, "cause we got
a big day for you, big guy.

224
00:08:41,055 --> 00:08:42,666
I got a bunch
of errands to run,

225
00:08:42,753 --> 00:08:45,190
but Alan is gonna take you
to the store

226
00:08:45,277 --> 00:08:47,018
and buy you a new backpack.

227
00:08:47,105 --> 00:08:49,237
I saw one that looks
just like Yoda.

228
00:08:49,324 --> 00:08:51,805
[imitates Yoda]:
To school you will wear it.

229
00:08:51,892 --> 00:08:53,241
Okay.
Hmm.

230
00:08:53,328 --> 00:08:55,461
What are you eating?

231
00:08:55,548 --> 00:08:58,420
Show it to me.

232
00:08:58,507 --> 00:08:59,770
Is that a cookie?

233
00:09:01,206 --> 00:09:02,773
Where did you get a cookie?

234
00:09:05,950 --> 00:09:08,692
Louis, where did you get
a cookie?

235
00:09:10,650 --> 00:09:13,218
Hey, uh, Louis,
why don't you go get dressed

236
00:09:13,305 --> 00:09:15,307
and-and I'll make you
some oatmeal,

237
00:09:15,394 --> 00:09:16,917
and then you can get going.

238
00:09:17,004 --> 00:09:18,136
Okay.

239
00:09:18,223 --> 00:09:19,485
Oh, and-and
don't forget

240
00:09:19,572 --> 00:09:20,704
to brush your teeth.

241
00:09:20,791 --> 00:09:22,357
And-and wash your hands.

242
00:09:22,444 --> 00:09:24,098
Oh, and put on clean underwear.

243
00:09:24,185 --> 00:09:25,839
Clean underwear?

244
00:09:25,926 --> 00:09:28,015
We're going to Target,
not the White House.

245
00:09:28,102 --> 00:09:31,149
Why would you give him a cookie
for breakfast?

246
00:09:31,236 --> 00:09:34,413
I couldn't help it.
He gave me orphan face.

247
00:09:34,500 --> 00:09:36,720
[Cockney accent]: Please, sir,
can I have a cookie?

248
00:09:36,807 --> 00:09:39,723
Me tum-tum is all empty
and growly.

249
00:09:39,810 --> 00:09:42,029
When it comes to Louis,
we have to be a team.

250
00:09:42,116 --> 00:09:44,379
If I make a rule,
you got to have my back.

251
00:09:44,466 --> 00:09:46,294
You're right, you're right,
and-and from now on,

252
00:09:46,381 --> 00:09:48,688
I will ignore him
like I ignore all those calls

253
00:09:48,775 --> 00:09:49,994
from the collection agency.

254
00:09:50,081 --> 00:09:52,518
Great. Okay, now, please,

255
00:09:52,605 --> 00:09:54,302
today, just take him
to the store,

256
00:09:54,389 --> 00:09:56,304
get him a backpack,
and then bring him home.

